---
const decisions = [
  {
    question: "Why OP_NOP4 instead of OP_SUCCESSx?",
    answer:
      "OP_SUCCESSx triggers an unconditional script success in a pre-execution scan — Schnorr checks would never run on non-upgraded nodes. OP_NOP4 redefinition (the CLTV/CSV precedent) lets existing Schnorr checks execute normally, maintaining security during activation.",
  },
  {
    question: "Why is sha_annex omitted from the SPHINCS+ sighash?",
    answer:
      "SPHINCS+ signatures live in the annex. Including sha_annex in the sighash creates a circular dependency (the signature would hash itself). The annex bit in spend_type is still set (0x03) for domain separation, and Schnorr's sighash still includes sha_annex, locking annex contents.",
  },
  {
    question: "Why standard SLH-DSA over the smaller W+C variant?",
    answer:
      "Standard FIPS 205 algorithms (WOTS+, FORS) are fully NIST-reviewed with the same security level. W+C_P+FP saves ~670 bytes per signature and is documented as a drop-in future optimization in the BIP addendum.",
  },
  {
    question: "Why disable bare-key spending?",
    answer:
      "Bare-key outputs can't verify the internal key against the tweak — they would completely undermine the NUMS ban. BIP 341 already recommends against bare keys, wallets don't create them, and BIP 9 activation gives time to migrate.",
  },
];
---

<section class="border-t border-border py-20 md:py-28">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6">
    <div class="mb-16 text-center">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight md:text-4xl">
        Design Decisions
      </h2>
      <p class="mx-auto max-w-2xl text-text-secondary">
        Key architectural choices behind the soft-fork design.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-4">
      {decisions.map((d) => (
        <details class="group rounded-xl border border-border bg-surface-raised transition-colors hover:border-quantum/30">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer px-6 py-5 text-left font-medium select-none list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            {d.question}
            <span class="ml-4 text-text-secondary transition-transform group-open:rotate-45 text-xl leading-none">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 leading-relaxed text-text-secondary">
            {d.answer}
          </div>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
